The paper presents a dataset for autonomous mobile robotics in agricultural scenes, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The dataset includes synchronized readings of several sensors, including a stereo camera, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper mentions that the dataset was conceived to provide a benchmark and contribute to research in agricultural SLAM and sensor fusion, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions that the dataset was created to address a lack of realistic sensor data in agricultural environments, which suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
